The paper discusses the analysis of multi-view classifiers, which is a topic related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of Gaussian priors and logarithmic determinant inequalities suggests a focus on statistical learning theory, which is a subfield of machine learning. The evaluation of the presented bounds on benchmark data suggests a focus on computer vision and natural language processing, which are subfields of artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
